quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  23,75,"And were We to have mercy upon them and remove whatever harm is upon them, surely they would continue to wander aimlessly while exceeding all limits."
  23,76,"And most surely We gripped them with punishment, but they did not surrender to their Lord, nor do they supplicate<i>(Him) </i>"
  23,77,"until, when We have opened before them a gate of intense punishment, they suddenly despair."
  23,78,"And it is He Who initiated for you<sup>pl </sup>the hearing and the sight<i>(s) </i>and the burning hearts; scarcely do you give thanks!"
  23,79,"And it is He Who scattered you<sup>pl </sup>on earth, and to Him you will be herded."
  23,80,"And it is He Who gives life and causes death, and to Him is the alternation of night and day. Do you<sup>pl </sup>not reason?"
  23,81,"Rather, they said the like of what the ancients had said."
  23,82,"They said, “Can it be thatwhen we have died and become dust and bones, can it be that{1}we will really be resurrected?",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Nafie’, Al-Kesa’i and Ya’qub read it as: “‘Can it be that when we have died and become dust and bones we will really be resurrected?’” Ibn Amer and Abu Ja’far read it as: “‘When we have died and become dust and bones, can it be that we will really be resurrected?’”]
  23,83,"Most surely, we were promised this before, we and our forefathers—these are nothing but legends of the ancients.”"
  23,84,"Say<sup>sg </sup>, “To whom does the earth and everyone in it belong, if you<sup>pl </sup>happen to know?”"
  23,85,"They will say, “To Allah.” Say<sup>sg </sup>, “Will you never remember{1}?”",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: All except for Hafs, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “Say<sup><small>sg</small></sup>, ‘Will you not constantly remember?’”]
  23,86,"Say<sup>sg </sup>, “Who is the Lord of the seven heavens and Lord of the Great Throne?”"
  23,87,"They will say, “To{1}Allah.” Say<sup>sg </sup>, “Will you never be mindful<i>(of God) </i>?”",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Abu Amr and Ya’qub read it as: “They will say, ‘Allah.’”]
  23,88,"Say<sup>sg </sup>, “In whose hand is the dominance of everything, and He grants refuge but cannot be granted refuge, if you happen to know?”"
  23,89,"They will say, “To<sup>a </sup>Allah.” Say<sup>sg </sup>, “Then are you bewitched?”",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Abu Amr and Ya’qub read it as: “They will say, ‘Allah.’”]
